{
  "id": "date_set",
  "title": "JS Date Set Methods",
  "group": "JS Dates",
  "content": [
    { "type": "h1", "text": "JavaScript Date Set Methods" },
    { "type": "p", "text": "Date set methods allow you to modify parts of an existing Date object. Each set method changes the date in place and returns the new timestamp in milliseconds." },

    { "type": "h2", "text": "setFullYear()" },
    { "type": "p", "text": "The setFullYear() method sets the year of a date. It can optionally set month and day as well." },
    { "type": "example", "title": "setFullYear()", "code": [
      "const d = new Date();",
      "console.log(\"Before:\", d.toDateString());",
      "",
      "// Set year only",
      "d.setFullYear(2025);",
      "console.log(\"After setFullYear(2025):\", d.toDateString());",
      "",
      "// Set year, month, day",
      "d.setFullYear(2025, 11, 25);",
      "console.log(\"After setFullYear(2025, 11, 25):\", d.toDateString());"
    ] },

    { "type": "h2", "text": "setMonth() and setDate()" },
    { "type": "p", "text": "setMonth() sets the month (0-11) and optionally the day. setDate() sets the day of the month. Setting setDate(0) gives you the last day of the previous month." },
    { "type": "example", "title": "setMonth() and setDate()", "code": [
      "const d = new Date(\"2024-06-15\");",
      "",
      "// Set month (0 = January)",
      "d.setMonth(0);",
      "console.log(\"January:\", d.toDateString());",
      "",
      "// Set date",
      "d.setDate(28);",
      "console.log(\"28th:\", d.toDateString());",
      "",
      "// Get last day of current month",
      "const lastDay = new Date(2024, 2, 0);",
      "console.log(\"Last day of Feb 2024:\", lastDay.getDate());",
      "",
      "// Add days by setting date beyond range",
      "const d2 = new Date(\"2024-01-31\");",
      "d2.setDate(d2.getDate() + 1);",
      "console.log(\"Jan 31 + 1 day:\", d2.toDateString());"
    ] },
    { "type": "note", "text": "If you set a value beyond its range, JavaScript automatically adjusts the date. For example, setDate(32) in January will roll over to February 1." },

    { "type": "h2", "text": "setHours(), setMinutes(), setSeconds()" },
    { "type": "p", "text": "These methods set the time components of a date. Each accepts optional additional parameters for the smaller time units." },
    { "type": "example", "title": "Time Set Methods", "code": [
      "const d = new Date(\"2024-06-15T10:30:00\");",
      "console.log(\"Before:\", d.toTimeString());",
      "",
      "// Set hours",
      "d.setHours(14);",
      "console.log(\"After setHours(14):\", d.toTimeString());",
      "",
      "// Set minutes",
      "d.setMinutes(45);",
      "console.log(\"After setMinutes(45):\", d.toTimeString());",
      "",
      "// Set seconds",
      "d.setSeconds(30);",
      "console.log(\"After setSeconds(30):\", d.toTimeString());",
      "",
      "// Set hours, minutes, seconds at once",
      "d.setHours(8, 0, 0, 0);",
      "console.log(\"After setHours(8,0,0,0):\", d.toTimeString());"
    ] },

    { "type": "h2", "text": "Comparing Dates" },
    { "type": "p", "text": "Dates can be compared using comparison operators or by comparing their timestamps with getTime(). Two Date objects are never equal with === even if they represent the same time." },
    { "type": "example", "title": "Comparing Dates", "code": [
      "const d1 = new Date(\"2024-06-15\");",
      "const d2 = new Date(\"2024-12-25\");",
      "const d3 = new Date(\"2024-06-15\");",
      "",
      "// Direct comparison works with < and >",
      "console.log(\"d1 < d2:\", d1 < d2);",
      "console.log(\"d1 > d2:\", d1 > d2);",
      "",
      "// === does NOT work for equality",
      "console.log(\"d1 === d3:\", d1 === d3);",
      "",
      "// Use getTime() for equality check",
      "console.log(\"d1 equals d3:\", d1.getTime() === d3.getTime());",
      "",
      "// Check if a date is in the past",
      "const past = new Date(\"2020-01-01\");",
      "console.log(\"Is past:\", past < new Date());"
    ] },

    { "type": "h2", "text": "Practical Date Manipulation" },
    { "type": "p", "text": "By combining set methods with get methods, you can perform common date operations like adding days, months, or finding the start/end of a period." },
    { "type": "example", "title": "Practical Date Operations", "code": [
      "// Add 7 days to a date",
      "const d = new Date(\"2024-06-15\");",
      "d.setDate(d.getDate() + 7);",
      "console.log(\"Plus 7 days:\", d.toDateString());",
      "",
      "// Add 3 months",
      "const d2 = new Date(\"2024-06-15\");",
      "d2.setMonth(d2.getMonth() + 3);",
      "console.log(\"Plus 3 months:\", d2.toDateString());",
      "",
      "// Get start of day",
      "const startOfDay = new Date(\"2024-06-15T14:30:00\");",
      "startOfDay.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);",
      "console.log(\"Start of day:\", startOfDay.toISOString());",
      "",
      "// Get end of day",
      "const endOfDay = new Date(\"2024-06-15T14:30:00\");",
      "endOfDay.setHours(23, 59, 59, 999);",
      "console.log(\"End of day:\", endOfDay.toISOString());"
    ] },

    { "type": "table", "rows": [
      ["Method", "Description"],
      ["setFullYear(year, month, day)", "Sets year, optionally month and day"],
      ["setMonth(month, day)", "Sets month (0-11), optionally day"],
      ["setDate(day)", "Sets day of month (1-31)"],
      ["setHours(h, m, s, ms)", "Sets hours (0-23), optionally m/s/ms"],
      ["setMinutes(m, s, ms)", "Sets minutes (0-59)"],
      ["setSeconds(s, ms)", "Sets seconds (0-59)"],
      ["setMilliseconds(ms)", "Sets milliseconds (0-999)"],
      ["setTime(ms)", "Sets date from milliseconds since epoch"]
    ] },

    { "type": "exercise", "question": "How do you properly check if two Date objects represent the same date?", "options": ["d1 === d2", "d1 == d2", "d1.getTime() === d2.getTime()", "d1.equals(d2)"], "answer": 2 }
  ]
}
